goals.question: What is the relationship between departure delay and arrival delay?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of departure_delay vs arrival_delay
goals.rationale: This helps us understand if there is a correlation between departure delay and arrival delay. It can help us identify if a delay in departure leads to a delay in arrival.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight cancellations?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of cancelled vs not cancelled flights
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights were cancelled and how many were not. It can help us identify if there are any patterns or reasons for flight cancellations.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airlines in the dataset?
goals.rationale: This tells us which airlines are represented in the dataset and how many flights each airline has. It can help us identify if there are any airlines that are overrepresented or underrepresented in the dataset.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', y='arrival_delay')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between departure delay and arrival delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='cancelled', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Not Cancelled', 'Cancelled'])
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight cancellations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    airline_counts = data['airline'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(airline_counts, labels=airline_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airlines in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
